description.plain: MOONLIGHT is a song I waited a very long time to release. It was made in the midst of a very depressing period in my life, but I was on the tail end of it. It’s about reaching your goals and striving for more and making peace with your darkness. There’s always light in the darkness. Hence, MOONLIGHT.

description.plain: This song is a tribute to the anime “Slam Dunk” which features the protagonist Hanamichi Sakuragi. In the show, the character trains wearing running shoes, which are later destroyed in the end of the practice match against Ryonan. He then starts wearing Air Jordan Nikes, and “Sixes” is an era of the shoe series known as “Air Jordan VI.”  When Graveheart proclaims, “I got my sixes on, I feel like Sakuragi,” he is stating that when he has his own Air Jordan VI’s on his feet, he feels like the unstoppable protagonist. The anime’s title is also referenced in the chorus.
